INSERT INTO `question_translations` VALUES (1,'App\\Models\\Question',1,'en','Which of the following are programming languages?','QST-000001','Python, JavaScript, and PHP are programming languages.','HTML is a markup language and CSS is a style sheet language.','Think about what is used to write software applications.',NULL),(2,'App\\Models\\Question',2,'en','The Great Wall of China can be seen from space.','QST-000002','This is a popular myth.','The Great Wall is not visible from space with the naked eye.','Consider the scale of the wall compared to other structures.',NULL),(3,'App\\Models\\Question',3,'en','Which ocean is the largest on Earth?','QST-000003','The Pacific Ocean covers more than 30% of Earth\'s surface.','The Pacific Ocean is the largest ocean.','It covers one-third of the Earth.',NULL),(4,'App\\Models\\Question',4,'en','Mount Everest is the tallest mountain in the world.','QST-000004','Mount Everest stands at 8,849 meters above sea level.','Mount Everest is indeed the tallest mountain above sea level.','It is located in the Himalayas.',NULL),(5,'App\\Models\\Question',5,'en','Which of the following are chemical compounds?','QST-000005','Compounds contain more than one element chemically bonded.','O₂ and He are elements, not compounds.','Look for substances with multiple element symbols.',NULL),(6,'App\\Models\\Question',6,'en','The Earth revolves around the Sun.','QST-000006','Earth completes one revolution around the Sun in 365 days.','This is the heliocentric model of our solar system.','It takes about a year.',NULL),(7,'App\\Models\\Question',7,'en','Which gas is most abundant in Earth\'s atmosphere?','QST-000007','Nitrogen makes up about 78% of Earth\'s atmosphere.','Nitrogen is the most abundant atmospheric gas.','It makes up most of the air we breathe.',NULL),(8,'App\\Models\\Question',8,'en','Humans have 46 chromosomes.','QST-000008','Humans typically have 23 pairs of chromosomes, totaling 46.','Each cell contains 46 chromosomes in total.','It is less than 50.',NULL),(9,'App\\Models\\Question',9,'en','Which part of the cell contains genetic material?','QST-000009','The nucleus contains DNA, the genetic material.','The nucleus houses the cell\'s genetic instructions.','It is often called the brain of the cell.',NULL),(10,'App\\Models\\Question',10,'en','The American Civil War ended in 1865.','QST-000010','The Civil War ended in 1865 with the Union victory.','General Lee surrendered to General Grant in April 1865.','It was during the 19th century.',NULL),(11,'App\\Models\\Question',11,'en','Who discovered America in 1492?','QST-000011','Christopher Columbus reached the Americas in 1492.','Columbus made four voyages to the Americas.','He sailed under the Spanish flag.',NULL),(12,'App\\Models\\Question',12,'en','Which empire was ruled by Genghis Khan?','QST-000012','Genghis Khan founded and ruled the Mongol Empire.','The Mongol Empire stretched from Eastern Europe to the Sea of Japan.','It was one of the largest empires in history.',NULL),(13,'App\\Models\\Question',13,'en','The Renaissance began in Italy.','QST-000013','The Renaissance started in Italy in the 14th century.','Italian city-states like Florence were centers of Renaissance culture.','Think of Florence and Venice.',NULL),(14,'App\\Models\\Question',14,'en','What is the largest continent on Earth?','QST-000014','Asia is the largest continent by area and population.','Asia covers about 30% of Earth\'s total land area.','It contains China, India, and Russia.',NULL),(15,'App\\Models\\Question',15,'en','The Nile is the longest river in the world.','QST-000015','The Nile River stretches over 6,600 km through northeastern Africa.','The Nile is the longest river at approximately 6,650 km.','It flows through Egypt and Sudan.',NULL),(16,'App\\Models\\Question',16,'en','Sahara is the largest desert in the world.','QST-000016','The Sahara in Africa is the largest hot desert by area.','The Sahara covers about 9 million square kilometers.','It is located in Northern Africa.',NULL),(17,'App\\Models\\Question',17,'en','Which country has the largest population?','QST-000017','China has the largest population in the world, over 1.4 billion people.','China has been the most populous country for centuries.','It is in East Asia.',NULL),(18,'App\\Models\\Question',18,'en','Which of the following numbers are prime?','QST-000018','Prime numbers have only 1 and themselves as divisors.','2, 3, and 5 are prime numbers.','Check divisibility.',NULL),(19,'App\\Models\\Question',19,'en','The sum of angles in a triangle is 180 degrees.','QST-000019','Every triangle has angles that add up to 180°.','This is a fundamental property of triangles.','Basic geometry principle.',NULL),(20,'App\\Models\\Question',20,'en','What is the area of a rectangle with length 5 and width 3?','QST-000020','Area = length × width = 5 × 3 = 15.','The area of a rectangle is calculated by multiplying its dimensions.','Multiply length and width.',NULL),(21,'App\\Models\\Question',21,'en','Sin(90°) equals 1.','QST-000021','The sine of 90 degrees is 1.','On the unit circle, sin(90°) = 1.','Think of the unit circle.',NULL),(22,'App\\Models\\Question',22,'en','HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language.','QST-000022','HTML is the standard markup language for documents on the web.','HTML provides the structure for web content.','It is used to create web pages.',NULL),(23,'App\\Models\\Question',23,'en','Which company created the iPhone?','QST-000023','Apple introduced the iPhone in 2007.','Steve Jobs unveiled the first iPhone at MacWorld 2007.','Think of the company with a fruit logo.',NULL),(24,'App\\Models\\Question',24,'en','The first computer was created in the 21st century.','QST-000024','The first computers were created in the mid-20th century.','ENIAC, one of the first computers, was completed in 1945.','Think of ENIAC from the 1940s.',NULL),(25,'App\\Models\\Question',25,'en','Which of these are web browsers?','QST-000025','Chrome, Firefox, and Safari are web browsers.','Photoshop is an image editor and Excel is a spreadsheet application.','Think about how you access websites.',NULL),(26,'App\\Models\\Question',26,'en','A football team has 11 players on the field.','QST-000026','Both soccer and American football have 11 players per team on the field.','This is standard for association football (soccer).','Count the positions.',NULL),(27,'App\\Models\\Question',27,'en','Which country won the 2022 FIFA World Cup?','QST-000027','Argentina won the 2022 FIFA World Cup in Qatar.','Argentina defeated France in the final.','The team was led by Lionel Messi.',NULL),(28,'App\\Models\\Question',28,'en','The Olympics are held every 4 years.','QST-000028','The Summer and Winter Olympics each occur every 4 years.','The Olympic Games follow a quadrennial cycle.','Think of the cycle.',NULL),(29,'App\\Models\\Question',29,'en','Which sports use a racket?','QST-000029','Tennis, badminton, and squash all use rackets.','Golf uses clubs and swimming uses no equipment.','Think about hitting a ball or shuttlecock.',NULL),(30,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',1,'en','<p>Which of the following are programming languages?</p>','QST-000030','<p>Several of these are widely used programming languages.</p>','<p>Python, JavaScript, and PHP are programming languages, while HTML is a markup language and CSS is a style sheet language.</p>','<p>They are used to write software applications.</p>',NULL),(31,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',2,'en','The Great Wall of China can be seen from space.','QST-000031','This is a myth. It cannot be seen from space with the naked eye.','False, the Great Wall is not visible from space without aid.','It is a myth.',NULL),(32,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',3,'en','____ wrote the play \"Romeo and Juliet\" and ____ wrote \"Pride and Prejudice\".','QST-000032','William Shakespeare wrote \"Romeo and Juliet\" and Jane Austen wrote \"Pride and Prejudice\".','The correct answers are William Shakespeare for the first blank and Jane Austen for the second blank.','They are both famous English authors.',NULL),(33,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',4,'en','Which continent is the Sahara Desert located in?','QST-000033','The Sahara Desert is located in Africa.','Correct answer is Africa.','It is the second-largest continent.',NULL),(34,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',5,'en','Which of the following planets are known as gas giants?','QST-000034','Gas giants are large planets primarily composed of hydrogen and helium.','Jupiter and Saturn are classified as gas giants.','They are located in the outer part of the solar system.',NULL),(35,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',6,'en','<p>Mount Everest is the tallest mountain in the world.</p>','QST-000035','<p>This is true.</p>','<p>Correct answer is True.</p>','<p>It is located in Nepal.</p>',NULL),(36,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',7,'en','Which ocean is the largest on Earth?','QST-000036','The Pacific Ocean is the largest.','Correct answer is Pacific Ocean.','Covers one-third of the Earth.',NULL),(37,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',8,'en','Fill in the blanks: The currency of Japan is ____ and the currency of the USA is ____.','QST-000037','Japan uses the Yen and the USA uses the Dollar.','The correct answers are Yen for Japan and Dollar for USA.','Japan starts with Y and USA currency is very common.',NULL),(38,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',9,'en','Which of the following are programming languages?','QST-000038','Several of these are widely used programming languages.','Python, JavaScript, and PHP are programming languages, while HTML is a markup language and CSS is a style sheet language.','They are used to write software applications.',NULL),(39,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',10,'en','The Great Wall of China can be seen from space.','QST-000039','This is a myth. It cannot be seen from space with the naked eye.','False, the Great Wall is not visible from space without aid.','It is a myth.',NULL),(40,'App\\Models\\QuizQuestion',11,'en','____ wrote the play \"Romeo and Juliet\" and ____ wrote \"Pride a